Remove stem, seeds and membrane from the red bell pepper. Finely julienne. Slice the red onion into thin slivers. In a large Tupperware bowl, toss with the balsamic vinegar. Trim green beans and blanch them by dropping them into boil water for 2 minutes. Drain and toss them in with the onions and peppers. Let the vegetables marinate for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Toss them a couple of times if you remember. When ready to serve, toss in the Carb Well Italian Dressing.